CSS PROPERTIES WITH EXPLANATION

1. color: Sets the color of the text inside an element.
Example: color: red; or color: #333;

2. background-color: Sets the background color of an element.
Example: background-color: lightblue;

3. width: Sets the width of an element.
Example: width: 400px; or width: 80%;

4. height: Sets the height of an element.
Example: height: 200px; or height: auto;

5. border: Adds a border around an eleme
Example: border: 2px solid black;

6. border-radius: Rounds the corners of an element.
Example: border-radius: 10px;

7. padding: Sets the space between content and border.
Example: padding: 20px; or padding: 10px 20px;

8. margin: Sets space outside the border (between elements).
Example: margin: 20px; or margin: 10px auto;

9. background-image: Sets an image as the background.
Example: background-image: url("image.jpg");

10. background-size: Defines how the background image should be scaled.cover, contain, auto
Example: background-size: cover;

11. background-repeat: Specifies whether/how the background image repeats.Values: repeat, no-repeat, repeat-x, repeat-y
Example: background-repeat: no-repeat;

12. background-position: Sets the starting position of a background image.Values: center, top, left, right, bottom
Example: background-position: center;

13. background: A shorthand for all background properties in one line.
Example: background: url("img.jpg") no-repeat center/cover;

14. font-size: Sets the size of the text.
Example: font-size: 16px; or font-size: 1.5em;

15. font-weight: Sets the thickness of the text.
Values: normal, bold, 100â€“900
Example: font-weight: bold;

16. text-align: Aligns the text horizontally inside its container.
Values: left, right, center, justify
Example: text-align: center;

17. display: Specifies how the element should be displayed.
Values: block, inline, inline-block, flex, none
Example: display: flex;

18. justify-content (used with flexbox): Aligns items horizontally in a flex container.
Example: justify-content: center;

19. align-items (used with flexbox): Aligns items vertically in a flex container.
Example: align-items: center;


22. line-height: Sets the height between lines of text.
Example: line-height: 1.5;

24. position: Specifies the positioning method. Values: static, relative, absolute, fixed, sticky
Example: position: absolute;

25. top, bottom, left, right: Used with positioned elements to define placement.
Example: top: 10px;
